      <h1>Field of Dreams ~ Achievements</h1>
      <h2>Achievements for Esperado Farm:</h2>
      <p>
      The following is a brief outline of the major achievements in recent years:
      </p>
      <ol>
      <li>
        A farm that was bought and could be put into a trust.
      </li><li>        
        The beneficiaries are the children.
      </li><li>        
        The farm can only belong to the children (under it's care).
      </li><li>        
        Now having nineteen children at school.
      </li><li>        
        Having the main house replaced after burning down (thanks to SASOL).
      </li><li>        
        The ability to look after children for ten years.
      </li>
      </ol>
      <h2>International Volunteers:</h2>
      <p>
      We have been able to get volunteers from different countries internationally to teach our children and the children at the local school in our community.
      </p>
      <a href='volunteers.html' title='About the Volunteers' class='aRight linkNext'>Read more about the Volunteers</a>
      <br class='brB' />
      <h2>Creation of the vegetable garden:</h2>
      <p>
      We have started a vegetable garden which will help supplement the children's diet as well as help the local community with the surplus.
      </p>
      <a href='garden.html' title='Read more about the garden' class='aRight linkNext'>Read more about the garden</a>
      <br class='brB' />
      <h2>Internally generated income:</h2>
      <ol>
      <li>
        Building of a road stall to sell our and the community's arts and crafts.
      </li><li>
        Manufacture of stock, maxi and block bricks.
      </li><li>
        Sale of livestock born and raised in our farmyard.
      </li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Field of Dreams farmyard:</h2>
      <p>
      The creation of our farmyard with various animals which helps the children deal with what they have experienced in their often traumatic histories. This has also helped facilitate visits from local schools to teach their children about farm animals and their environment.
      </p>
      <a href='farmyard.html' title='Read more about the farmyard' class='aRight linkNext'>Read more about the farmyard</a>
      <br class='brB' />
      <h2>Caregivers, Care centres and Orphanages:</h2>
      <ol>
      <li>
        Linking up with other caregivers as a support, to assist one another.
      </li><li>
        Linking up with other care centres and orphanages, so that they can also have the privilege to experience the beauty of nature in their school holidays.
      </li><li>
        Creating opportunities where other caregivers can meet people that want to get involved with projects concerning children.
      </li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Poverty stricken community bordering farm:</h2>
      <ol>
      <li>
        Teaching the community to create a safe and clean environment for themselves.
      </li><li>
        Creation of work in the community (temporary and permanent).
      </li><li>
        Teaching the community to protect local nature.
      </li><li>
        Providing help to elderly and single parents.
      </li><li>
        Providing help with the Aids / HIV epidemic.
      </li><li>
        Assisting with all their emergencies to the best of our abilities.
      </li><li>
        If no Government transport is available, we get the sick to Barberton Hospital.
      </li><li>
        We assist with burials.
      </li><li>
        We provide burial grounds.
      </li><li>
        We provide borehole water.
      </li><li>
        All excess food and second-hand clothing is donated.
      </li><li>
        Provide meals for hungry children.
      </li><li>
        Assisting children with school registration fees and clothes. 
      </li>
      </ol>
